Governor Purdue thanks for the increase in Smart Start Funds.  The monies that came to Jones County are crucial in the implementation of all of our programs.  Though our county is small and our funds are equally as small they impact the children and families birth to 5 in Jones County in a tremendous way.  Ten years ago no star rated child care providers were in Jones County.  Today of the six (6) Centers in Jones County four (4) are Five Star and two (2) are Four Star. Four of our centers are More at Four Sites in the public schools providing Pre-K to each of our four townships.  Our parents in the past four years have attended a minimum of four high quality parent workshops here at Smart Start in our Family Support Activity and M@4 contract and without this additional money we would have had to cease this project.  Educating the child without educating the parent for some families is getting us no where fast. Thanks, again. Remember

 Research studies have documented that children who have spent time in high quality child care environments have lasting benefits from the experience.  This makes it

even more important for children in the neediest families (like those in Jones County) to have options in selecting a high quality child care setting without regards to the cost of high quality child care. 

