Governor, please allow me to join the many others who have expressed their appreciation for your support with the 2% reversion relief for the North Carolina Community College System.  As a president of one of the 58 institution who had experienced a very large enrollment increase due to the state of our economy, I can tell you having access to these funds for the 2010 spring semester will allow my college to employ faculty members and strategic support personnel to help serve the additional patrons who have turned to their community college for help.  The funds will also help us purchase some strategic equipment that is needed to provide up-to-date instruction for our students - one of the legislative priorities in the community college state budget.

Please know that the Board of Trustees and I are acutely aware of the challenges you have had to cope with since assuming the Governor's duties. In many instances, there have been no easy answers and we commend you on the work you are doing to keep North Carolina appealing from an economic development, tourism, and family living standpoint.  Press on.

